SIMPLE: wherret
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Wherret
<hw>Wher"ret</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[From
<er>Whir</er>.]</ety> <altsp>[Also spelled <asp>whirret</asp>.]</altsp>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>To hurry; to trouble; to tease.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Bickerstaff.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To box (one) on the ear; to strike or box (the ear);
<as>as, to <ex>wherret</ex> a child</as>.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Wherret</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Wherret
<hw>Wher"ret</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A box on the ear.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Beau. & Fl.</au></rj> <altsp>[Also spelled
<asp>whirret</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Wherry</ent>⟦br⟧
